txt.en: Anírwen is at the market near the docks of Dol Amroth, on the eastern side of the city.\n\nYou should bring the fresh catch to Anírwen.
'A nice haul for one day! Make sure you come back again, dear.'
This is a good place for fishing
Catch fish off the wharf of Dol Amroth ([placeholder]/[placeholder])

'Do you enjoy fishing? If so, you are welcome to cast your line off our wharf any day you like!\n\n'There is a stair that leads to a low dock, with a few rowboats tied up. In my opinion, that is the best place to fish. You should give it a try, my dear! Nothing soothes the soul like a bit of ocean fishing.'
Anírwen has invited you to do some fishing off the wharf of Dol Amroth.
An ideal fishing spot can be found on the low dock where the rowboats are tied up, south-east of Anírwen.\n\nYou should fish on the low dock.
